# 1000G CNV Reference Builder

🧬 Automated workflow for constructing a **high-quality WGS reference cohort** from the **1000 Genomes Project high-coverage (~30×) GRCh38 dataset** for **copy number variation (CNV) baseline generation**.

This project provides a reproducible workflow to download, batch-process, and quality-control unrelated high-coverage genomes for building a **Panel of Normals (PoN)** suitable for **CNVkit** and other read-depth–based CNV callers.

Designed as a **portfolio-ready bioinformatics utility** inspired by real-world genomics workflows used in research and clinical sequencing environments.

---

## 📌 Overview

Read-depth–based CNV detection tools require a robust reference baseline to reduce sequencing noise and improve copy number calling accuracy.

This workflow automates:

✅ Selection of **unrelated founder genomes**  
✅ Download of **1000 Genomes high-coverage (~30×) WGS CRAM files**  
✅ Batch-based downloading for reproducibility  
✅ Coverage quality control (QC)  
✅ Preparation for downstream **CNV reference generation**

---

## ⚙️ Workflow

```text
1000 Genomes High Coverage (2504)
                ↓
Founder / Unrelated Sample Selection
                ↓
Random Sample Selection
                ↓
Batch Generation
                ↓
CRAM + CRAI Download
                ↓
Coverage Quality Control
                ↓
Reference Cohort Selection
                ↓
CNVkit Reference Generation
```

